<item>
            <title>[LU-18529] FLSOM: Strict SOM for closed files</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18529</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This ticket is for a possible feature called &quot;file level SOM&quot;, which would use the file level replication layout IO control mechanisms to allow strict SOM for files not being actively written.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would apply the SOM after last close, using the FLR mechanisms to avoid the issues with evicted clients which normally prevent safe use of SOM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not clear if this would offer enough performance benefit to be worth the engineering effort, so the first step will be some benchmarking.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
